<item>
            <title>[SPARK-1615] Very subtle race condition in SparkListenerSuite</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1615</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Much of SparkListenerSuite relies on LiveListenerBus&apos;s waitUntilEmpty() method. As the name suggests, this waits until the event queue is empty. However, the following race condition could happen:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(1) We dequeue the event&lt;br/&gt;
(2) The queue is empty, we return true&lt;br/&gt;
(3) The test asserts something assuming that all listeners have finished executing (and fails)&lt;br/&gt;
(4) The listeners receive the event&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has been a possible race condition for a long time, but for some reason we&apos;ve never run into it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
